Okay, let's break down the request of building a personalized DAX parameter category. DAX (DynamoDB Accelerator) parameter groups allow you to manage and modify the configuration of your DAX cluster. A "personalized" parameter category implies we need to create a new DAX parameter group rather than using the default.  We'll need to define the parameter group's family (which dictates which DAX clusters it can be associated with), a name for the group, and then define any parameters we want to customize within that group.

Here's a Terraform configuration to achieve this. I will include comments to explain the code.  I'll start with a basic parameterized group creation and include a sample parameter modification.

```hcl
resource "aws_dax_parameter_group" "example" {
  name   = "my-custom-dax-param-group" # Replace with your desired parameter group name
  family = "dax1.1"               # The DAX cluster family (e.g., dax1.1, dax1.0)

  description = "Custom DAX parameter group for my application"

  parameter {
    parameter_name = "node_to_node_encryption" # Example parameter to customize.  Check AWS documentation for valid parameters.
    parameter_value = "yes"                     # Change "yes" to "no" if not needed.  Values are case sensitive.
  }

  tags = {
    Name        = "My Custom DAX Param Group"
    Environment = "Development"
  }
}
```

