3.  **Security Group:** We'll define a security group to allow inbound MySQL traffic (port 3306) from anywhere (for simplicity, though in production, you'd restrict this to known IP ranges).
4.  **RDS Instance:**  We'll provision a MySQL 5.7 RDS instance with a 500 GB storage size.  It will be associated with the two subnets we created for high availability and the security group we defined.  We will also enable public accessibility for demonstration purposes.
